        <description>My Linux Mint installation on my laptop has a wee problem with the extreme resolution of the laptop display. This is 3072 by 1920 (16:10) and when an application is opened on the laptop screen, it is tiny. I need to fix it, so this is what I do when I install a new release.
Display Properties LM -&amp;gt; Preferences -&amp;gt; Display. Settings tab: Make sure &amp;ldquo;Enable fractional scaling controls&amp;rdquo; is off.</description>
        
